For two independent exponential random variables with rate \(\lambda\), the minimum \(Y_1\) follows an exponential distribution with rate \(2\lambda\). Thus, \(E(Y_1) = 1/(2\lambda)\). Substituting \(\lambda = 1/2\) gives \(E(Y_1) = 1/(2 \times 1/2) = 1/1 = 1\).

