**************
The solution uses Chebyshev's inequality to find a lower bound for \(P(|Y / n - 0.25| < 0.05)\) when \(n = 500\) and \(Y \sim b(n, 0.25)\). The variance of the sample proportion \(X = Y / n\) is calculated as \(\sigma^2 = 0.000375\), and with \(\varepsilon = 0.05\), \(\sigma^2 / \varepsilon^2 = 0.15\). Applying Chebyshev's inequality gives \(P(|X - \mu| < \varepsilon) \geq 1 - 0.15 = 0.85\). Thus, the lower bound is 0.85.

