 The unit of the answer should be  .
Solution: The sample mean \(\bar{X}\) follows an approximately normal distribution due to the Central Limit Theorem, with mean \(\mu_{\bar{X}} = \mu = 54.030\) and standard error \(\sigma_{\bar{X}} = \frac{\sigma}{\sqrt{n}} = \frac{5.8}{\sqrt{47}} \approx 0.846\).

