- Of those with normal blood pressure, 11% have an irregular heartbeat, so the percentage with both normal blood pressure and irregular heartbeat is 11% × 65% = 7.15%.

The percentage with irregular heartbeat and low blood pressure is found by subtracting the known irregular heartbeat cases from the total irregular heartbeat:  
17% - 5.95% - 7.15% = 3.90%.

The percentage with low blood pressure is 19%, which includes both regular and irregular heartbeats. Therefore, the percentage with low blood pressure and regular heartbeat is:  
19% - 3.90% = 15.10%.

Rounded to a reasonable number of significant figures (based on input data), this is 15.1%.

