- P(both orange) = number of ways to choose 2 orange balls from 2 / total ways to choose 2 balls from 4 = C(2,2) / C(4,2) = 1 / 6.
- P(at least one orange) = 1 - P(both blue) = 1 - C(2,2)/C(4,2) = 1 - 1/6 = 5/6.
- Therefore, P(both orange | at least one orange) = (1/6) / (5/6) = 1/5.

Evaluating 1/5 to a single numeric value gives 0.2. This is exact and requires no rounding.

Summary: The final answer is $0.2$
